# validate-doc-references.sh ignore list — one regex per line.
#
# Each pattern is matched against:
#   - v1 scope: the captured `platform/...` reference string
#   - v2 scope: the resolved project-root-relative path of a markdown link
#               target (anchor stripped). Falls back to the raw target string
#               when the resolver returns nil.
#
# Use sparingly. Prefer fixing the reference in the source file to silencing
# it here. The validator's value is exactly its noisiness about drift.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# v1 — bare `platform/...` reference findings
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Known-historical-drift: this reference in platform/templates/knowledge/README.md
# points at a workflow guide that was never authored. Tracked for a future
# follow-up (either author the missing guide or remove the reference). Ignored
# here so the new validator can be wired into CI without first fixing every
# historical drift in the repository — a separate concern.
^platform/workflow/knowledge-capture-pattern\.md$

# Illustrative example paths used inside platform/workflow/troubleshooting.md
# to document what a broken-reference error looks like. These appear in inline
# backticks (not fenced blocks) so the v1 validator sees them; they are
# pedagogical strings, not real references. Anchored exact-match so a real
# same-named file would still need to exist on disk if it were ever introduced.
#
# Note: v2 strips inline backtick spans before extracting links, so these
# v1-era entries no longer apply to v2's link-extraction path. Retained for
# safety against any v1 code path that still surfaces these strings.
^platform/foo/example\.md$
^platform/workflow/missing-guide\.md$

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# v2 — renderer-aware findings to triage
#
# These entries were seeded when validate-doc-references.sh v2 first ran
# against the harness's own tree. Each is a real renderer-fragile link that
# v1 did not catch. They are exempted here so v2 can be wired into CI without
# blocking on the long-tail cleanup; the canonical triage list lives in
# platform/validators/README.md "Known v2 exclusions to triage".
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CHANGELOG.md:179 — `[\`docs/adr/\`](docs/adr/)` — trailing-slash directory
# target. GitBook 404s on `<target>/README.md` lookups for this pattern.
# Follow-up: link to a representative ADR (e.g. ADR-0010) or author
# docs/adr/README.md as a canonical landing page for the ADR series.
^docs/adr$
